# Filament — the keys voice, ELECTRIC: none of the glassy sine purity.
# Narrow pulse (0.18) into a hot resonant filter is the electricity —
# the squelch lives in the 1.4 resonance and the fast +1.8 octave
# filter ping, not in bell partials. A detuned saw underneath beats
# against the pulse (6 cents — audible instability), sine an octave
# down for weight. PWM churns slowly so no two notes have the same
# waveform. Driven at 2.6 into the ladder: heat, not glass. A little
# spring, because electricity lives in amps with springs.
waveform 1
pulse_width 0.18
osc2_wave 2
osc2_pitch 0
osc2_level 0.35
osc3_wave 0
osc3_pitch -12
osc3_level 0.3
detune 6
sub 0.2
circuit 1
key_track 0.7
osc_fm 0
sync 0
ring 0
glide 0
attack 0.003
decay 0.9
sustain 0.3
release 0.3
filter_env 1.8
filter_attack 0.001
filter_decay 0.18
filter_sustain 0.2
filter_release 0.25
cutoff 900
resonance 1.4
drive 2.6
saturation 1.2
hpf 55
volume 0.5
octave 4
noise 0
fuzz 0
spring 0.15
lfo_rate 0.9
lfo_shape 0.5
lfo_pitch 3
lfo_filter 0
lfo_pwm 0.25
